Furthermore, for 3 colours,  a.a.s.\ ${\mathcal{G}}(n,p) \to \left(P_{(1/2 -\alpha) n}\right)_3$, which is optimal and implies that $c_3 = 1/2$.
\end{theorem}
\noindent
Furthermore, we conjecture that $c_r = n/R(P_n,r)$ for any $r \ge 2$, which is true for $r=2$~\cite{L15} and for $r=3$, due to the above theorem.

