\begin{proof}[Sketch of the proof of Theorem~\ref{thm:mono_comps}]
This is basically the proof of Theorem~\ref{thm:multi_Gnp} with Corollary~\ref{cor:erdos_gallai} replaced by Lemma~\ref{lem:mono_comps}. 
We find a monochromatic spanning tree on $(1/(r-1) - \varepsilon r^2)s$ vertices in the cluster graph, and then we replace each edge by a long path (in a bipartite graph). All those paths intersect yielding a large monochromatic component.
The sharpness follows immediately from the sharpness of Theorem~\ref{thm:G77}.
